Yes!  And more…   Notice we use the letters A-G of the alphabet to name each note.  When we reach the end, we repeat.  When you have C to C, that distance is called an OCTAVE.  It spans the distance of 8 notes on the staff.
(This particular set of notes is also called a C Major Scale.  We'll explore that in a later lesson.)
